The article discusses how 141 countries from around the world have issued a call for a comprehensive and lasting peace in Ukraine, in line with the principles of the UN Charter. These nations are demanding Russia's immediate withdrawal from all of Ukraine's territory. The article emphasizes that the international community is committed to upholding shared values such as sovereignty, independence, and territorial integrity, as well as accountability for violations of international law. The vote in favor of the UN General Assembly resolution is seen as a strong show of support for Ukraine and a defense of freedom worldwide.